detaileddescription.para:
Before calling any function on a hash operation object, the application must initialize it by any of the following means:

Set the structure to all-bits-zero, for example: psa_hash_operation_toperation;
memset(&operation,0,sizeof(operation));


Initialize the structure to logical zero values, for example: psa_hash_operation_toperation={0};


Initialize the structure to the initializer PSA_HASH_OPERATION_INIT, for example: psa_hash_operation_toperation=PSA_HASH_OPERATION_INIT;


Assign the result of the function psa_hash_operation_init() to the structure, for example: psa_hash_operation_toperation;
operation=psa_hash_operation_init();

Before calling any function on a MAC operation object, the application must initialize it by any of the following means:

Set the structure to all-bits-zero, for example: psa_mac_operation_toperation;
